                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.21/470: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-23T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1919, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 20, 4 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d729fn12">Not printed.</note> Strictly
                    confidential.</p>
                <p>From Johnson.<note n="13" xml:id="d729fn13">Hallett Johnson, diplomatic officer
                        on duty in the Department.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The President has instructed the Department to take up treaty with Senate
                    immediately. Mr. Polk has written Senators Lodge and Knox giving them present
                    situation in full and urging action.</p>
                <p>Mr. Lodge’s attitude appears to be favorable though one or two points remain to
                    be cleared up. Will keep you informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
